rComments: Being in orchestra for about 8 years prior to taking this class really helped me. He didn't seem to care much about the students. right off the bat he said he wouldn't answer emails from us. but the class was easy. he was clear.

Boring lecature and hard to pay attention to. Not very organized either. Listening is a little difficult, but I think that the only reason I did well is because I was in Orchestra for 10 years prior to attending college. Unless you enjoy classical music, I do not recc.

I as well had heard many good things about this class.  Unfortunately, it was all under Turino and Solis.  Dietrich has found a way to bore the h3ll out of me in what I think could be a very interesting class.  Very vague multiple choice tests.  Hope you have a good TA or you're screwed. don't recc.
He's a good teacher, he explains things well and tells you what you need to know for tests.  With effot the class should be very doable.
